Class HttpNetworkLocation

    SecureHttpNetworkLocation
    public class HttpNetworkLocation
extends NetworkLocation
implements Resourceful
    An HTTP network location.

    Access

    HTTP network locations can be accessed as resources with resource(). The can also be accessed with the HTTP access methods GET, PUT and POST:

    • get() - A HttpGetResource with default content type and access constraints
    • get(String) - A HttpGetResource with the given content type
    • get(NetworkAccessConstraints) - A HttpGetResource with the given access contraints
    • get(NetworkAccessConstraints, String) - A HttpGetResource with the given content type and access constraints
    • post() - A HttpPostResource with default content type and access constraints
    • post(String) - A HttpPostResource with the given value to post
    • post(String, String) - A HttpPostResource with the given content and value to post
    • post(NetworkAccessConstraints) - A HttpPostResource with the given constraints
    • post(NetworkAccessConstraints, String, String) - A HttpPostResource with the given constrains, content type and value to post
    • put(String, String) - A HttpPutResource with the given content type and value to put
    • put(NetworkAccessConstraints, String, String) - A HttpPutResource with the given access constraints, content type and value to put
